>[Question]
>Where do I start as I don't believe completing the square in this 
>case will work.  I am supposed to find the center and radius of the 
>circle described by the equation and graph each equation.  I was 
>given X squared plus Y squared = 49
>
>[Difficulty]
>Where do I start as I cannot complete the square?
>
>[Thoughts]
>X + Y = 7

Hello LeAnn,

x^2+y^2=49

has center (0,0) and radius 7.

The general formula is

(x-h)^2+(y-k)^2=r^2.

This is the equation of a circle with center (h,k) and radius 4.


